article.description: — Rytis Petraitis scored 20 points off of the bench to lead Air Force to an 81-67 victory over Tarleton on Sunday night.
article.headline: Petraitis sparks Air Force to 81-67 victory over Tarleton
article.linkText: Petraitis sparks Air Force to 81-67 victory over Tarleton
article.story:
COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. -- — Rytis Petraitis scored 20 points off of the bench to lead Air Force to an 81-67 victory over Tarleton on Sunday night.

Petraitis had 10 rebounds for the Falcons (8-4). Jake Heidbreder had 17 points. Ethan Taylor scored 11 with seven rebounds.

Tiger Booker finished with 18 points for the Texans (5-6). Jakorie Smith added 15 points, while Shakur Daniel scored 12.

Heidbreder scored 11 in the second half to help the Falcons rally from a 38-37 halftime deficit.
